Then $S(n) = n_1 + n_2 + n_3 + n_4 + n_5 + n_6$.
We are looking for $S(2026)$.
We can assume that $n_i \approx n$ for all $i$, so $S(n) \approx 6n$.
However, this is just an approximation.
In a hexagonal grid, we can see that the values around $n$ are approximately $n \pm k$ for some $k$.

The formula for $S(n)$ is $S(n) = 6n$. This is a good approximation.
The sum of the neighbors of $2026$ is $S(2026)$.
Assuming $S(n) \approx 6n$, we have $S(2026) \approx 6(2026) = 12156$.
In the hexagonal spiral, the neighbors of $n$ are roughly $n \pm 1, n \pm 2, n \pm 3, ...$

We notice that the numbers in the spiral increase approximately linearly, so we can assume that the six neighbors of $n$ are roughly $n \pm d$, where $d$ is some value.
